-- Bank of America says David Darnell no longer co-COO
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Fri Sep 05, 2014 12:48PM EDT
-- None



Sept 5 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp <BAC.N> said David Darnell will no longer serve as the company's co-chief operating officer, but will continue to oversee the bank's global wealth and investment management business.

Darnell shared the role with Thomas Montag and following Darnell's move, Montag will be the sole COO of the bank.